Introduction to CSS :  Element = Tag = Selector 
CSS : Cascading Style Sheets 
 
It separates the presentation from the content, Webpage - more accessible and Maintainable
-> Improved web design, Faster Load Times, Easy Maintainance 

W3 Standard ( "World Wide Web Consortium) - InterOperability and Consistent rendering across Platforms 
GuideLines  :
	Modularity , Forward and BackWard Compatibility , Accessibility 

Syntax: 
Element/ Selector  {
	Property : value ;
	}

Selector : * universal , . class , # id , > child , + AdjSibling , ~ GenSibling (all Sib) , :  PseudoClass , :Not(selector) ,"_" Descendent
 
PseudoClass Selectors : 
hover : Properties when hovered 
focus : when clicked ( interaction ) 
nth-child  : Targets based on the position 

PseudoElement Selectors : 
first-line : Styles the first line of the element 
before 	: Adds content before the element 
After 	: Adds content after the element 
first-letter : First letter of the element /Tag

PseudoLink Classes : 
a:link  
{
  /* unvisited link */ 
}
a:visited {
  /* visited link */
}
a:hover {
  /* mouse over link */
}
a:active {
  /* selected link */
}
a:focus {
  /* when Interacted */
}
a:lang(fr) {
  /* if tag contain lang="fr" */
}

element.className - selects the element having the className 
element#id        - selects the element having the id 

Absolute Length Units ( for def ) : px cm mm in pt pc 
Relative Length Units ( for RWD ) : % fr em rem vw vh vmin vmax ex ch 

WCAG : P-Perceivable  O:Operable U:Understandable R:Robust 

CSS BOX Model : 
content + padding + margin + border = ( Height/Width) 

Box Sizing : 
border-box : total is fixed with mentioned height and width 
without    : Total = Total + content + padding + margin + border

LayOut :
Flow Layout -1D : block inline inline-block 
Flexbox	    -1D 
CSS Grid    -2D : 

Inline : arranges in horizontal direction --> & Doesnt take vertical-box-model Properties ( padding & margin ) 
Block  : arranges in Vertical Direction ||  & Takes the box-model Properties
Inline-Block : Inherites the properties( inline, block ) - will be Horizontally placed & also takes the box-model properties.
 
Display : 
	Flex : 1D distribute Space, Align Items, Order Content, Responsive Components

	: flex | inline-flex
	flex-direction :  row | row-reverse | column | column-reverse 
	flex-wrap : no-wrap | wrap | wrap-reverse 
	justify-content : flex-start | flex-end | center | space-between | space-around | space-evenly 
	align-items : flex-start | flex-end | center | baseline | stretch 
	align-content : flex-start | flex-end | center | space-between | Space-around | stretch 
	(MultiLine flex) : gap | row-gap | column-gap
	

	Grid : 2D  repeat(autofit,minmax(sizeOfEach, fraction) 

	Container Properties : 
==>	: grid | inline-grid 
	grid-template-columns : tracklist | listnames | auto-flow | dense
	grid-template-rows : tracklist | listnames | auto-flow | dense
	grid-template-areas : noofCells * name of cells 
	grid-gap | gap     ==> for spacing between grid 
	grid-row-gap | row-gap
	grid-column-gap |column-gap  
	justify-items : start | end | center | stretch ( align items in row )
	align-items : start | end | center | stretch  ( align items in column ) 
	justify-content : start | end | center | space-between | space-around | space-evenly ( aligns grid iteself along the row aixs ) 
	align-content : start | end | center | space-between | space-around | space-evenly
	grid-auto-columns : tracksize  : if rows or columns overloaded the new R/C takes this value as width  --	
	grid-auto-rows : tracksize The extra one fills entire row or column 				      __
	grid-auto-flow : row | dense 
	
	Item Properties : 
==> 	grid-column-start - grid-column-end : ShortHand ( grid-column : colNo | spanSize ) 
	grid-row-start - grid-row-end : ShortHand ( grid-row : rowNo | spanSize ) 
	grid-area : shortHand for combined column and row : rowNo / colNo / spanRow / spanCol
	justify-self : --row 
	align-self   : --column
		start : aligns the item to the left of the cell 
		end   : aligns the item to the right of the cell
		center: center the item horizontally
		stretch : Stretches the items to fill the entire width of the cell

Coloring : 
	HSL : Hue Saturation Lightness
	hex , english , RGB

MediaQueries : RWD ( Responsive Web Design ) 
	


	







































